name: Street Outlaws
overview: From a 1969 Chevy Nova to a race-ready farm truck, the vehicles - and their drivers - come in all shapes and sizes and have one thing in common: the need for speed. But according to the STREET OUTLAWS of Oklahoma City - home to one of the largest undercover street racing rings in America – if you’re not on “the list,” you don’t matter. The “list” contains the 10 fastest street-racing cars in Oklahoma City and they are the best of the best. Not only will these guys will do anything -ANYTHING- to get ranked on this list, they’ll do whatever it takes to STAY ranked. Street racing comes first - before family, before friends and before work. The stakes are high and these drivers will put everything on the line to get to top, where there can only be one #1.

seasons.name: Season 18
seasons.overview: Street Outlaws explores the world of street racing in Oklahoma City where, after throwing out the top 10 list, the 405 competes in a high-speed, high-stakes qualifier for a chance to race in America’s List.

episodes.name: Midnight Riders
episodes.overview: Fights break out in the opener of this series exploring the world of underground street racing.

episodes.name: Young and Old Blood
episodes.overview: Varley is forced to quit street racing; Chuck is targeted by the police.

episodes.name: King of the Streets
episodes.overview: Doc and Murder Nova face off.

episodes.name: Murder the Nova
episodes.overview: Murder Nova draws unwanted attention; Varley and Farmtruck prepare for a rematch.

episodes.name: Stand Your Ground
episodes.overview: Chuck and Flip cause trouble at a poker tournament.

episodes.name: Racer's Revenge
episodes.overview: Doc and Shawn face off in a rematch; Derek calls out Farmtruck.

episodes.name: Last Car Standing
episodes.overview: Derek challenges Varley; Dave calls out Shawn.

episodes.name: Interstate Showdown
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN take a road trip through Texas.

episodes.name: Lonestar Smackdown
episodes.overview: In the season premiere, Farmtruck and AZN must face-off against one of four newbie racers who want to get on the top ten list. Big Chief gets a callout via an online video from a Texas race club who think they can take on the 405’s best. Old state rivalries lead to big brawls when Texas racers LMR want to change the rules on the OKC guys.

episodes.name: Midwest Fireworks
episodes.overview: Big Chief strikes a deal with loudmouth racer Freakin’ Rican, allowing him to call out #10 Farmtruck in exchange for bootleg fireworks. There’s a shakeup in the middle of the list when #8 Derek gets called out by newcomer #9 Andrade and #6 Chuck gets called out by #7 Varley. Big Chief, Murder Nova, and Chuck spy on a Varley test hit but when the Gold Car veers off the road, things go terribly wrong.

episodes.name: Sonoma Mr. Nice Guy
episodes.overview: After an expensive overhaul of his car, #2 Murder Nova calls out #1 Daddy Dave in an unforgettable rematch showdown. Freakin’ Rican finally gets his shot when he calls out #10 Farmtruck, but an AZN joyride jeopardizes the Farmtruck’s gatekeeper standing.

episodes.name: Fastest Chick in OKC
episodes.overview: Farmtruck gets called out by a local legend.

episodes.name: Showdown Lowdown
episodes.overview: Doc races Monza; Daddy Dave and Murder Nova face off.

episodes.name: Drag Week
episodes.overview: Big Chief resurrects his first race car.

episodes.name: Papa's Got a Brand New Bug
episodes.overview: AZN and Farmtruck build a Volkswagen race car.

episodes.name: Straight Out to Cali
episodes.overview: The OKC crew visit Compton, Cal.; AZN and Farmtruck head to Chicago.

episodes.name: The Rise of the Crow
episodes.overview: Street Outlaws returns with Big Chief stepping down as racemaster to pursue the list in his twin turbo-charged Pontiac a.k.a "The Crow". AZN, Farmtruck and the "Dungbeetle" have a run-in with police while testing. Varley’s son/driver Tony quits, leaving the team high and dry. Tina drops off the list, leaving an opportunity for new racers and familiar faces to race-off round-robin style for the coveted #10 spot

episodes.name: Go Back to Tulsa
episodes.overview: Track racers from Tulsa call out the 405 with hopes of taking down the "fastest street-raced cars in the country". Farmtruck and AZN attempt a garage sale. Both Murder Nova and Chuck upgrade to twin turbo.

episodes.name: Top 5 List Shake-Up
episodes.overview: Farmtruck tries to shake things up.

episodes.name: The Mouthy Dirty South
episodes.overview: The team visits New Orleans.

episodes.name: What's Up Doc?
episodes.overview: Doc is determined to make a comeback with the Street Beast. Big Chief and Kamikaze decide it's time for the El Camino to race for the list. Farmtruck and AZN go after redemption with an old rival with the Dung Beetle.

episodes.name: Dallas Cash Days
episodes.overview: OKC racers take on the fastest of the south at the annual Cash Days race. While fishing for street races and fast cash, Farmtruck and AZN meet their match.

episodes.name: Big Chief vs Murder Nova
episodes.overview: Big Chief finally calls out his best friend Murder Nova, in hopes of taking the #1 spot from Daddy Dave.  Drag racer Kayla Morton and former Texan Boosted GT take their shot at the list.

episodes.name: It's Good to Be the Chief
episodes.overview: Big Chief targets Monza and Daddy Dave in the Season 3 finale. Meanwhile, Varley upgrades his car.

episodes.name: Down from Chi-Town
episodes.overview: Trash-talking street racers from Chicago take on their Oklahoma City rivals; the Farmtruck reels in a Ferrari and a Camaro.

episodes.name: Shut Your Death Trap
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and Chuck face off.

episodes.name: Ova for Murder Nova?
episodes.overview: Shawn considers dropping off the list.

episodes.name: Small Tire Shootout
episodes.overview: Spanish Chuck puts on a Small Tire Shootout, where cars with small tires race; Farmtruck and Asian attend a car show in Kansas

episodes.name: Gatekeeper Gate
episodes.overview: Big Chief calls a second race night in one week to defuse rising tensions between racers who want a shot at the Top Ten List.

episodes.name: Vocal Local Yokels
episodes.overview: Street Outlaws is a driver’s seat view into the world of American illegal street racing. The first season takes place in Oklahoma City, which boasts having the “fastest street cars in the country”. From a 1969 Chevy Nova, to an incognito, race-ready farm truck

episodes.name: Hearse and the Wichita Curse
episodes.overview: Big Chief gets a call out from the 316 area code, Wichita, Kansas.  Some of the 405's fastest racers must take on guys with names like the Murder 56 and Superman. Farmtruck and AZN get some seat time in the haunted hearse

episodes.name: Let Them Eat Crow!
episodes.overview: As the season comes to a close, everybody makes one final push to move up on the list.

episodes.name: The Southeast's Fastest: Part 1
episodes.overview: It’s the biggest, most O.G. Cash Days ever! 2 days of racing and 16 of the fastest racers in the Southeast square off.  The 405's fastest set their sights on bringing the prize home and being crowned the fastest street raced car in the southeast.

episodes.name: The Southeast's Fastest: Part 2
episodes.overview: On the final night of Cash Days, the remaining 405 racers put their reputation on the line as one of them tries to win $16,000 and be crowned the fastest street racer in the Southeast.

episodes.name: Bumper to Bumper: The Secrets of the Street Outlaws
episodes.overview: A behind the scenes look into the 405 racers’ lives, with never-before-seen footage, sneak peeks and best-of moments.  Their day jobs and financial sacrifices are revealed as well as their families feelings about racing.

episodes.name: Not So Big Easy
episodes.overview: Chief organizes a Nationwide Call Out for a $50,000 pot. Chief gets a new paint job and Dave calls him out. Farmtruck and Asian go fishing in Memphis. Later, the 405 travel south to take on Kye Kelly and friends.

episodes.name: She's a Good Girl
episodes.overview: Chief confirms another driver for the nationwide call out. Farmtruck & AZN play around with the Mad Scientist's new toy: a Tri-Powered Trike. On race night, Shawn tries to get the Murder Nova back to the top of the list.

episodes.name: Small Tires, Big Dreams
episodes.overview: Boosted wants to be the first small tire car to crack the Top 5 on the List and make 405 History. Farmtruck is depressed from the death of Louise, so AZN brings someone new into the family. Dave opens up a new shop and has a new racecar.

episodes.name: Texas Grudge
episodes.overview: Boosted has set up Grudge Races down in Fort Worth, Texas against some old school grudge racers, but get more than they bargain for. Race night gets downright wild in the Lone Star State.

episodes.name: To Be #1 Or Not To Be #1
episodes.overview: Big Chief gets a racer for the Nationwide Callout: Petey Smallblock, representing the Northeast. Doc is ready to take on Big Chief for the #1 spot. Farmtruck and AZN go fishing, but do not get any bites, until a Dodge Neon falls into their lap.

episodes.name: Fear and Gloating in Las Vegas
episodes.overview: The guys take on some of the fastest street racers in Las Vegas; Farmtruck and AZN want to leave their mark on the city.

episodes.name: Angel City Danger
episodes.overview: The 405 guys head to California to take on smack talking street racers from LA. On race night, heated exchanges escalate, with trash talking, spitting incidents, and nearly a full out brawl. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN take a trip to Hollywood.

episodes.name: Round Robin Ridiculousness
episodes.overview: When Daddy Dave drops off the list, everyone moves up. Leaving an open #10 spot. Big Chief decides to hold the largest round robin in 405 history to determine who is worthy and the winer must race the ultimate gatekeeper, Farmtruck.

episodes.name: 405 vs. Middle of 'Murica
episodes.overview: The 405 gets called out by 7 of the fastest racers from Colorado, Wyoming, Missouri and Kansas for a street showdown. Kamikaze needs to make money and brings back El Camino. Farmtruck and AZN prank Big Chief and Shawn by buying a "More-Door" Nova.

episodes.name: The Nationwide Callout
episodes.overview: It’s on! The 405's Top 5 takes on the Nation's fastest cars for bragging rights and huge payouts. Farmtruck and AZN pull a prank on Chief and Shawn to get back at them. Big Chief's got a score to settle with his biggest rival, Kye Kelly.

episodes.name: Kansas City Barbecue
episodes.overview: The 405 travels to Kansas City to accept a challenge of some smacktalking racers. Farmtruck and AZN take on an elderly couple in a Hotrod. The 405 plan to prove their claim of being the "nation's fastest" by hosting the biggest Cash Days event in history.

episodes.name: No Rhino, No Cry
episodes.overview: The 405 List gets big shake-ups as everybody wants to move up, especially Dominator, who has been winning a lot recently. AZN is fed up with Suzi's biting antics so Farmtruck gets a dog trainer. Kamikaze takes a crack at the #10 spot.

episodes.name: Import this!
episodes.overview: The 405 get an unusual callout from a bunch of mouthy racers with super fast imports. Murder Nova, Chief, Chuck, Shane, Kamikaze and Boosted are in for a shock when the ricer cars prove to be faster than anyone imagined.

episodes.name: David & Goliath vs. the 405
episodes.overview: Daddy Dave is finally ready to unveil his new racecar, "Goliath", and controversy brews as he wants to bully his way up the list. Farmtruck and AZN are convinced the firehouse is haunted and they call a medium to rid their adobe of evil spirits.

episodes.name: Top of the List to Ya
episodes.overview: It's another 405 Top Ten list shake-up! Daddy Dave takes on Derek, Monza calls out Murder Nova, Boosted takes on Doc, Shane must race Chuck and lots of other surprise races all over the list. Will Big Chief get dethroned? Will Dave continue to climb?

episodes.name: Fear The Reaper
episodes.overview: After Daddy Dave crashes his new car, Chief attempts to reunite Dave with Jackie Knox so he can drive the Sonoma. Another racer, The Reaper, takes a shot at the list and tempers flare. Farmtruck attempts to surprise AZN by trying to locate his first car.

episodes.name: $50K, All The Way!
episodes.overview: Dissatisfied with the Nationwide Callout results, Big Chief decides to host an epic Cash Days with 32 cars all competing for $50K. Daddy Dave & The Sonoma, Kye Kelly with the NOLA crew & the OKC's fastest racers bring the heat. Who will be crowned the fastest in the nation?

episodes.name: Jumping The Shark Pool
episodes.overview: Chief has an idea to make the list even faster... The Shark Pool. Every week a group of hungry racers will be looking to take the #10 spot. Doc and Monza battle. Farmtruck schools a shark pool racer in regards to an old debt.

episodes.name: Sharks After Dark
episodes.overview: With the Shark Pool becoming more popular, Chief must host two race nights. Henson, Your Mom, and Chuck 55 all show up to take on the gatekeeper, leaving Shane fighting for survival. Chief and Shawn rematch for the #1 spot on the second race night.

episodes.name: Daddy Day Car
episodes.overview: Daddy Dave returns as part of the Shark Pool with Henson's Corvette "Plan B," along with new mother Tina Pierce. Boosted GT drops off the list. Farmtruck and AZN get a ricer rivalry between Jackie and Shane burns hot.

episodes.name: Rebirth of the Crow
episodes.overview: Chief decides to get a new car while the battle for the top list spots are heating up. Doc calls out #1 Shawn and Monza faces Reaper. Dave needs to get past Shane, while new shark Jeremy must race against the Farmtruck to get on the list.

episodes.name: The Crow Also Rises...
episodes.overview: Chief reveals his new car, The Crow Mod. Shawn calls out Doc and Reaper faces Monza. AZN and Farmtruck race the Dung Beetle against a car named "Bug Killer". Tensions rise between Dave's team and Reaper on race night, causing fights to breakout.

episodes.name: Ready, Set, Crow...
episodes.overview: All bets are off for the final race. Chief faces off against Farmtruck for the #10 spot. Rookie Jeremy calls out Dominator for the #6 spot. Reaper and Shane compete for the #5 spot. Shawn attempts another shot at #1.

episodes.name: Where the Streets Have No Name
episodes.overview: The list is shaken up when Daddy Dave pulls Henson's Plan B from the one spot and starts from the ten spot in his own car. Farmtruck and AZN faceoff. Also Doc and Shawn prepare to race for #1. Meanwhile, Chief gets ready for his long march up the list.

episodes.name: It's A Promod Party
episodes.overview: Going under the hood to find out what makes the cars fast; Farmtruck and AZN struggle to fix the Dung Beetle for fishing and set up some races to get out of paying for some tuning.

episodes.name: OH-HI-NO
episodes.overview: The 405 rushes to get ready after receiving a last minute call out from Ohio. Farmtruck and AZN go fishing for a hot rod and Kamikaze gets ready to bring the El Camino back. When the racers from Ohio arrive, the 405 try to prove again they are the fastest on the street.

episodes.name: I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For
episodes.overview: The list gets shaken up again. Shane finds himself in a grudge race, but things turn disastrous after the finish line. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN get called out and race night becomes hostile when Dave and The Reaper can't agree on a call out.

episodes.name: I Will Follow
episodes.overview: With Dave in the top 5 and Chief right behind at 6, the pressure is on the top racers to be ready for a show down. Chief and Boosted setup an emergency turbo school for a struggling Dominator. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN find themselves a flashy, orange fish.

episodes.name: 75,000 Reasons to Race
episodes.overview: The 405 are headed south to race at the Texas Motorplex in the American Outlaws Live event. More organized than the sport has ever been, this event may be a precursor to a national league of street racers.

episodes.name: Stuck In A Moment
episodes.overview: Frustration rises on the 405 list. Racers try to hang on instead of moving up. Famrtruck and AZN make some improvements to the Farmtruck and test it out in a fishing race. Things heat up on race night when Dave makes a callout for a race he has no intention of racing.

episodes.name: One
episodes.overview: The last list race of the season is here and that puts the pressure on everyone to make their final moves towards the top. Kamikaze and Farmtruck make triumphant returns to list racing and there will be a new number one on the 405 list.

episodes.name: Street Mission
episodes.overview: When JJ "Da Boss" from Memphis invites the 405 to race, the 405 leave their pro mods at home and head east to the craziest race ever. Chuck is eager to prove himself and the Memphis guys give the OKC racers a run for their money.

episodes.name: Put Up for Your City
episodes.overview: Chief decides to organize a first of its kind team race off. Detroit, New York and California each bring a team to compete against the 405. Five of the 405's OG racers step up to prove that OKC has the fastest group of street racers in the country.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Part III
episodes.overview: The Street Outlaws agree to race the guys from Fast N' Loud. Farm truck and AZN start on their budget build to race Aaron Kaufman. Meanwhile, Chief and Shawn set out in search of the perfect car. When Chief hears rumors from Texas, he's not sure if he wants to build a car.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Part IV
episodes.overview: With only a week left, the teams at Midwest Streetcars and Farmtruck & AZN are scrambling to get their builds ready to race. With little experience building cars on a schedule, both teams are starting to think they may not finish their cars in time.

episodes.name: Mega Race Build Up
episodes.overview: With everyone in California, Chief and Richard get into it about who will drive their cars. Farmtruck and AZN are stuck waiting for Aaron. Then it's finally time for the drivers to strap in, pull up to the line and race to see who has what it takes to win.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: The Mega Race
episodes.overview: With everyone finally in California, Chief & Richard get into it about who will drive their cars, and Farmtruck & AZN have to wait on Aaron. Then, it's time for the drivers to strap in, pull to the line, and race to see who has what it takes to win.

episodes.name: From Mega to Street
episodes.overview: The new season of Street Outlaws is about to begin & the 405 is moving away from Pro-mods on the street, so Chief and Shawn take a look back at how far the 405 has come since before the show.  Then, we show some deleted scenes from the big Mega Race.

episodes.name: Start Me Up
episodes.overview: In the Season 9 premiere, the guys in the 405 make big changes. Chief decides to kick all the pro-mods off the list; and everyone loses their spots and have to race to find out where they belong on the list.

episodes.name: I Can't Get No Satisfaction
episodes.overview: After the list shakeup, the 405 has an entirely new list and everyone is still fighting to get to the top. Dave is down for repairs, so Chuck, Ryan, Shawn and Monza battle it out to try to take the top spot. Meanwhile, Doc tries to get himself out of the bottom five.

episodes.name: Get Off My Cloud
episodes.overview: Ryan and Chuck are getting ready to battle for the top spot again; and Farmtruck is feeling the heat at the bottom of the list and does everything he can to hold onto a spot on the list.

episodes.name: Brand New Car
episodes.overview: Chief is ready to take his new car up the list again, Reaper struggles to get his car ready for race night. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN think outside the box to round up some races for the Farmtruck, now that it is off the list.

episodes.name: Sympathy for the Devil
episodes.overview: When JJ and his racers from Memphis come to OKC for two nights of racing, everyone in the 405 has to step up and put it all on the line. After flagging and other technicalities cause drama, the 405 has to fight for every win.

episodes.name: Can't You Hear Me Knocking
episodes.overview: With Chief back on the list, he and Shawn map out a plan to get themselves back into the top spots. Farmtruck sets up AZN with a race against a doctor with a super car. On race night, Doc seems like he finally has his car figured out.

episodes.name: Time Is On My Side
episodes.overview: With only a few list races left, everyone is getting serious about moving up the list. AZN gets a new tune for the Dung Beetle and tests it out. On race night, when Doc gets in trouble, Chief pounces on the chance to make a big move up the list.

episodes.name: Street Fightin' Man
episodes.overview: The last list race of the season is here and everyone in the 405 is looking to make one last move towards the top. On race night, some of the top guys don't bring their cars and plans to move up the list blow up in Doc's and Chief's faces.

episodes.name: Midnight Rambler
episodes.overview: When JJ "Da Boss" comes to OKC from Memphis to host a race, everyone who's anyone in street racing shows up to compete. The racers will do anything to win with JJ going back to old school rules and a total of $60,000 on the line.

episodes.name: Smoked in Memphis
episodes.overview: The entire 405 crew heads Memphis, and that means they're racing on JJ's slick, asphalt road. When the 405's plan to stick together falls apart, they struggle to set up the right races and it looks like Memphis might get the best of them.

episodes.name: Going For The Jugular
episodes.overview: The first list race of the season; Shawn tries to jump on the No. 1 spot while Chief's car goes in for repairs; Doc tries to hold off on racing Reaper and chaos breaks out on race night

episodes.name: Down Is The New Up?
episodes.overview: Chief commits to fall down the list on purpose in order to race everyone he missed on his last trip to the top; Ryan and Chuck struggle to get their cars ready; Shawn goes after Chuck in an attempt to take the OG Murder Nova back to number one.

episodes.name: Bad Beets
episodes.overview: With Chief out of town, Chuck takes over as racemaster, but still has to defend number one. Farmtruck & AZN dig up a new kind of race. Then on race night, with racers missing, Monza & Dave jump into the top five while Ryan tries to take Chuck's Crown.

episodes.name: Bristol: Race to $100K
episodes.overview: The 405 head to Bristol, Tennessee to compete in the biggest no prep event in Street Outlaws history. With 32 of the baddest cars competing for $100K, the OKC racers give it all they've got in order to take the win. It's Bristol, Baby!

episodes.name: Rules Change
episodes.overview: With 32 of the baddest cars around competing for $100,000, the OKC racers give it everything they’ve got to take the win. It’s Bristol, Baby!

episodes.name: What's Up Doc?
episodes.overview: New rules mean that the racers at the top of the list are stuck waiting for callouts but there's plenty of drama in the bottom five. While Kamikaze struggles to make it to race night, Jeff Lutz and Dominator prepare to battle to get back on the list.

episodes.name: Outlaw Armageddon
episodes.overview: It's time for Outlaw Armageddon, the biggest & baddest No Prep race in the country, & the 405 gets ready for the race. Everyone who is anyone in the street & track races scenes comes to OKC to lay it all on the line and try to win the $40,000 prize.

episodes.name: Bottoms Up
episodes.overview: The new rules mean that the racers at the top of the list are held up waiting for callouts, but that means there's plenty drama in the bottom five. While Kamikaze struggles to make it to race night, Jeff Lutz and Dominator prepare to battle to get back on the list.

episodes.name: Armageddon to the End
episodes.overview: After the first round of Outlaw Armageddon, there are still 19 of the best racers in the country left to fight it out for the $40,000 pot. The remaining 405 racers must fight to defend their turf, because being beat at their home track isn't an option.

episodes.name: Daily Battles
episodes.overview: The 405 battle it out in OKC; Chief races AZN; Doc and Chuck meet up for the first time ever.

episodes.name: 99 Problems
episodes.overview: With only two list races left in the season, the drivers work to get their cars ready to race. Farmtruck and AZN prepare to race for some fishing. On race night, Ryan is getting ready to defend his number one spot and tempers flare between Doc and Monza.

episodes.name: Who Made These Rules?
episodes.overview: The final list race of the season is here and everyone is aiming to move up. Murder Nova races Farmtruck for the first time and Ryan fights to reclaim the #1 spot. Then, chaos breaks out when Doc refuses a callout.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Countdown To Motor Mega Week
episodes.overview: It's the countdown to Discovery's first Motor Mega Week and that means a sneak peek at all the action. It's full of motor madness, including 3 all-new series premieres, plus the season finale of Street Outlaws: Memphis and all-new American Chopper.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Start Your Engines
episodes.overview: Mega Race 2 starts with race master and NASCAR superstar, Kyle Busch.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 1
episodes.overview: After losing to the 405 during the last Mega Race, Richard Rawlings wants a rematch and this time, he's going after current #1, Ryan Martin. The guys at Misfit Garage also callout Farmtruck & AZN for a race of their own, where they each build a car.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 2
episodes.overview: The Gas Monkeys work to make sure their chassis will let the car drive straight, but weather prevents them from making any good test passes. Ryan and team head to Tucson to test the car in Arizona's warmer climate, but must work through some trials.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 3
episodes.overview: The Misfits start their build but tempers flare when an argument breaks out, threatening to stall the build completely. Farmtruck and AZN work on transforming the Gonorail into a functioning vehicle, but learn that this build will take extra work.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 4
episodes.overview: Farmtruck & AZN and the Misfits complete their builds and make some test hits, but struggle with technical issues that must be corrected. Ryan arrives in Phoenix along with some fellow 405 racers while the Gas Monkey crew heads to Arizona to race.

episodes.name: Team Gas Monkey
episodes.overview: Richard re-ignites the rivalry between Gas Monkey Garage and the Street Outlaws by challenging outlaw Ryan Martin to a drag race in his Demon Challenger.

episodes.name: Misfit Mischief
episodes.overview: The mechanics from Fired Up Garage are ready to rumble, when they get wind Richard Rawlings and the Street Racers from the 405 are holding a rematch. The Misfits challenge Farmtruck and AZN to an all out 30 lap, three-driver road course race.

episodes.name: The Fireball
episodes.overview: After getting called out by Richard Rawlings from Gas Monkey Garage, number one racer Ryan Martin has to work like crazy to get his car ready for the race. He and his team head out west to test, but it seems like everything is about to go wrong.

episodes.name: The Gonorail
episodes.overview: After accepting a challenge from the Misfits at Fired Up Garage, Farmtruck & AZN build themselves a road race vehicle. However, Farmtruck's vision to put a monorail car from the Oklahoma State Fair on wheels proves to be their biggest challenge ever.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Driver's Meeting
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN get ready for Mega Race 2.

episodes.name: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: The Mega Race 2
episodes.overview: It's finally time for Mega Race 2, and that means that the racers from Street Outlaws, Fast N Loud, and Misfit Garage are all in Arizona for the big race. It's Oklahoma vs. Texas, and these guys will do anything to win.

episodes.name: The Story of Street Outlaws
episodes.overview: The Street Outlaws go in depth into how the show began and talk about what happened when producers came to Oklahoma for the very first time. They talk about their favorite moments from the show, and about how Street Outlaws has changed them.

episodes.name: Playing Dirty
episodes.overview: When Reaper gets a smack talking call from a local dirt track owner, it turns into a dirt race challenge for the whole 405. After some testing, everyone from OKC comes to the track to try and prove they can be king of the street and king of the dirt.

episodes.name: Make My "Cash" Days
episodes.overview: Thirty-two of the fastest racers from around the country gather in OKC for the biggest street race of the year Cash Days. And, with $50,000 on the line, all the racers are prepared to push their cars to the limit to try and win it all.

episodes.name: Tech and Tune
episodes.overview: It's time for a new season of list racing in OKC and that means all the racers are upgrading and prepping their cars to be competitive. After lots of work, it's finally time to test the cars and see who's ready to dominate the list this season.

episodes.name: The Doc Amendment
episodes.overview: After a difficult end to last season's list racing, the 405 comes together to reassess the rules and make a plan to move forward. They all agree to a list shakeup, which means everyone loses his spot on the list and has to race to earn a new place.

episodes.name: No More Stalling
episodes.overview: After an unfinished list shakeup Ryan & Chief finally line up to race for #1. With the list complete, the 405 gets ready for their first list race of the season. But with no active callouts, it's going to be a fight for who has the right to move up.

episodes.name: Deja Vu
episodes.overview: It's a mad dash to make repairs as the top racers scramble to get ready to race. Meanwhile, Farmtruck & AZN head out of town to compete in a giant Daily Driver event. Then, on race night, the Reaper returns to go after #10, and Ryan has to defend #1.

episodes.name: Top Dom
episodes.overview: Reaper returns to go after No. 10, while Ryan has to defend No. 1.

episodes.name: Flor-I-Do
episodes.overview: With Florida racers coming to OKC, everyone in the 405 prepares for the first out of town race of the season. Farmtruck and AZN head out of town to get the Farmtruck ready for the race.

episodes.name: Asphalt Eruption
episodes.overview: Asphalt Eruption

episodes.name: Clashes And Crashes
episodes.overview: Clashes And Crashes

episodes.name: Oh, Canada!
episodes.overview: When a group of Canadian racers decide to come to OKC, the 405 has to prepare to defend the USA; taking big risks to show the Canadians that when it comes to street racing, America can't be beat.

episodes.name: "Tired" of Chief
episodes.overview: After the race against Canada, Dave and Ryan struggle to get their cars switched back to big tires in time for list racing. Monza pulls his car off the list, which lets all the racers below him move up, and Reaper faces an unexpected contender.

episodes.name: Down but Not Out
episodes.overview: As it gets closer to the last list race of the season, racers struggle with broken cars; when it's time to race, Shawn makes a stand and shows everyone else on the list what it means to race anytime, even if one has to beg to get one's car ready.

episodes.name: Chuckmate
episodes.overview: AZN and Farmtruck cast a wide net to go fishing. Monza pulls his car off the list, setting up an unexpected contender for Reaper.

episodes.name: Unfriended
episodes.overview: It's the last list race of the season, and that means all the racers are getting ready for their last chance to move up the list; after a season of game playing and drama, tension has never been higher between the racers in the 405.

episodes.name: Grudge Wars
episodes.overview: After a tough season of infighting and game playing, the racers of the 405 come together for a grudge race night, hoping to squash all the issues they have with each other.

episodes.name: Cash Days: The Daily Driver
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN are hosting another daily driver race, and this time, they've invited racers from all over the country to come to the 405 and race for $25,000. All the racers get their cars ready and cruise out to the race spot for the big event.

episodes.name: Bristol: Race to $200K
episodes.overview: The second annual Bristol No Prep race begins with 32 of the fastest men and women competing for a prize of $200,000; the competition heats up as racers push their cars round after round, adjusting their tunes for the track.

episodes.name: Eyes on the Prize (Bristol 2019, Part 1)
episodes.overview: The second annual Bristol No Prep Race begins with 32 of the fastest men and women competing for a giant, winner-take-all prize of $200,000; with so many heavy hitters in the field, the only certainty is that racers will give it their all to win.

episodes.name: Don't Rain on My Parade
episodes.overview: Sixteen racers move into round two of the Bristol No-Prep Race, and the competition heats up; however, when rain rinses the track clean, the racers have to adjust their tunes for the trickier track.

episodes.name: No Prep Kings: Mo' Money Mo' Memphis
episodes.overview: The No Prep Kings Points Championship continues in Memphis Tennessee, where racers compete for $40,000 and points in the championship. As racers move into round 2 the heat and humidity become more challenging as the track gets greasy and slicker.

episodes.name: No Prep Kings: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Racers arrive at Maple Grove Raceway for the 3rd event in the No Prep Kings series, but rain delays the start of the race. It’s all about tuning as the battle heats up to see who can take home valuable points and the $40,000 prize.

episodes.name: Sweet Tunes in Memphis
episodes.overview: Racers arrive at Maple Grove Raceway for the 3rd event in the No Prep Kings series, but rain delays the start of the race.

episodes.name: Riders on the Storm
episodes.overview: It’s all about tuning as the battle heats up to see who can take home valuable points and the $40,000 prize.

episodes.name: Pouring It On in PA
episodes.overview: Racers arrive at Route 66 Raceway outside of Chicago for the fourth race in the No Prep Kings series; when cold weather and rainy conditions make the track extra-sketchy, the racers have to be on their game if they want to make it to the finish line.

episodes.name: Speed Palace Royalty
episodes.overview: Racers enter round two of the fourth event in the No Prep Kings series; after a challenging round one, the track comes around; racers have to turn their cars up without blowing the tires off as they all chase points and the $40,000 prize.

episodes.name: Mile High Mayhem
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Morrison, Colorado for the next event in the No Prep Kings series, however, the high altitude means thin air and big problems for the racers who run turbos.

episodes.name: Driving High
episodes.overview: It's time for the finals rounds in the race for points and $40,000 at Bandimere Speedway, but challenging conditions and a lengthy schedule are knocking out cars left and right. However, the top racers won't let the high altitude get them down.

episodes.name: Tricky Tucson Track
episodes.overview: Racers are in Tucson, AZ for the sixth race in the points series, but the desert dust and heat mean a seriously sketchy surface. Racers will have to be on their game if they want to take home a win on the most challenging track they'll race.

episodes.name: Desert Dollars
episodes.overview: It's day two of the sixth race in the points series and when the sun comes out, the Tucson track gets even sketchier. And, with a rare chance to make up some serious ground, Mike Murillo is hoping to go rounds and earn some valuable points.

episodes.name: The Heart of It All
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Norwalk, Ohio for the seventh race in the No Prep Kings series and with only a few races left, the points race for the Championship is on. But, with a deceptively tricky track, the racers must find the right tune or risk going home.

episodes.name: Buckeye Battles
episodes.overview: Racers move into the second half of the seventh race in the No Prep Kings series, and with most of the top points leaders still in the race, the pressure is on for them to go all the way.

episodes.name: Carolina on My Mind
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Benson, North Carolina for the second to last No Prep Kings race of the season, but a hurricane passed through town right before the race making the track trickier than normal.

episodes.name: Coastin' in Carolina
episodes.overview: Racers are at GALOT Motorsports Park, and with most of the points leaders moving into the second half of the race, the pressure is on. It's the last race before the double points finale, so for anyone with their eyes on the prize, it's now or never.

episodes.name: Finally in Texas
episodes.overview: It's time for the final event of the No Prep Kings season, and the stakes have never been higher. This race is for double points, which means every round counts as Ryan Martin, Mike Murillo, and Larry Larson scramble to take home the $250,000.

episodes.name: Crowning the King
episodes.overview: After a dramatic round one, the race to the Points Championship is wide open. And, with everything on the line, the top racers are prepared to give everything they've got in order to earn the coveted title of No Prep King Points Champion.

episodes.name: Speedy's Strip
episodes.overview: Looking for a family friendly location for a race, JJ and the Memphis Street Outlaws decide to host an Arm Drop race at a local airstrip. It's Memphis against the world as they invite racers from all over to come out and compete for a $32,000 pot.

episodes.name: From Airstrip to Street
episodes.overview: Racers move into round 2 of JJ's Arm Drop at Speedy's Strip, and the Memphis Street Outlaws are representing well against competitors from all over. When rain moves in quickly and puts the race on hold, JJ decides to finish on the street.

episodes.name: Let's Get Ready to Crumble
episodes.overview: When Farmtruck finds a fleet of old cop cars at the salvage yard, he and AZN decide that the best use for them would be a giant demolition derby, the likes of which the 405 has never seen. Drivers from OKC, Texas, and Mississippi all get to work.

episodes.name: Down and Derby
episodes.overview: It's finally time for the Toilet Bowl 500, and the racers are ready to do some serious damage. Chuck and Reaper seem like early favorites since they brought such serious cars, but wildcards like Tina, Ed, and Monza take a stand.

episodes.name: Coming Back to Life
episodes.overview: When Big Chief gets a call from California street racer, Boddie inviting the 405 to come out West for a race, there's no way Chief can refuse. The OKC racers all pack up and head out for an epic night of racing with more than $20,000 on the line.

episodes.name: Money
episodes.overview: The 405 is in California taking on Boddie and his group of racers, but it hasn't been an easy night so far. This time around, there's more than just money on the line.

episodes.name: Bring The Boys Back Home
episodes.overview: The 405 is ready for another season of list racing, but this time they're hoping to put the past behind them, come together, and try to make street racing fun again. But on race night, the same old games threaten to break the 405 apart before they start.

episodes.name: Run Like Hell
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN head to Kansas to fish with the new and improved Gonorail. Back in Oklahoma, Ryan and Dominator repair broken cars in preparation for list racing, but when a driver gets out of control, the evening is brought to an abrupt end.

episodes.name: Time
episodes.overview: Monza gets a chance to come for the list after his wreck, Shawn makes plans to get back into the Top 5, Farmtruck and AZN find a fun use for discarded airbags. Things heat up on race night as drivers make up for the lack of racing the previous week.

episodes.name: Round and Around
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN invite the 405 racers out to Willow Springs International Raceway for a road race competition; the racers pair up to compete in a time-attack competition in which the pair with the fastest combined times will take home $10,000.

episodes.name: Burning Rubber Down Under
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN can't say no when they're invited to Summernats, an annual burnout competition in Australia; they buy a new truck, ship it to Australia and get it ready in time to learn the true definition of burning rubber.

episodes.name: Shine On You Crazy Diamond
episodes.overview: Ryan Martin looks over his car while Chief and Dave push each other in a competitive testing session, as they all get ready for another chance at No. 1. Then, when it’s time to race, the racers fight to move up the list until broken cars slow everyone down.

episodes.name: Dark Side of the Moon
episodes.overview: It's finally time for the last list race of the season, and the racers get their cars ready for the big race; Farmtruck and AZN fish out some fancy cars at cruise night; on race night, a costly mistake threatens to derail Chief.

episodes.name: Cash Days: Another Brick in the Wall
episodes.overview: OKC and Texas compete in an old-school Cash Days race; eight drivers from each state race for more than $30,000 and the chance to prove their state has the fastest racers, but a sketchy road throws a wrench into the works for both sides.

episodes.name: Cash Days: Comfortably Numb
episodes.overview: On the second night of Cash Days, 405 racers must match up and race, while still fighting to knock out the only remaining Texas driver; the sketchy road is still in play, and it becomes a tuner's game to see who can get down the street in one piece.

episodes.name: Win One For The Team
episodes.overview: The top No Prep racers gather at Maryland International Raceway for the first event of the season. Alliances form amongst veterans and newcomers alike, and tensions rise as each new faction plots its course to the top of the standings.

episodes.name: NOLA Rising
episodes.overview: Team OKC arrives in New Hampshire fired up after an explosive start at Maryland International Raceway the week prior. With Texas keen to strike back, Kye realizes the only way NOLA can compete is if they also band together.

episodes.name: The Crow Also Rises
episodes.overview: Big Chief is ready to make his No Prep debut as the racers roll into St. Louis for the third race of the season. NOLA is determined to deliver back-to-back upsets after the last race but the OKC and Texas aren't going down without a fight.

episodes.name: Lock It Up
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Idaho for the season's fourth race, and everyone is focused on chasing down Lizzy. Ryan Martin tries a tricky new setup that could make or break his chances. As OKC, Texas, and NOLA band together, a new faction of misfits forms.

episodes.name: Route 66 Showdown
episodes.overview: With the season half over and racers jockeying for points, the horseplay gets crazier than ever at Route 66 Raceway in Illinois. Lizzy and Team NOLA have been an unstoppable force so the competition is prepared to do anything to get ahead.

episodes.name: Mile-High Mischief
episodes.overview: A hostile points battle becomes even more intense as drivers struggle to adjust to the altitude at Colorado's Bandimere Speedway. With turbos and pro-chargers gasping for air, the season's most combative staging war has everyone scrambling.

episodes.name: Ruler of the Mountain
episodes.overview: Heading into the seventh race at Summit Motorsports Park in Ohio. Conditions remain unforgiving as the racers move into round two at Colorado's Bandimere Speedway. With so much on the line, even those who are struggling will stop at nothing to win and be crowned King or Queen of the Mountain.

episodes.name: Fireball Flameout
episodes.overview: With two races left in the season, drivers are hustling to rack up points. On the brink of another championship, Ryan feels the pressure. Team NOLA forms an unexpected alliance in an attempt to increase their chances of winning an NPK trophy.

episodes.name: Don't Choke
episodes.overview: Ryan rolls into the final event at the top of the leaderboard and with each round worth double points, the pressure is on to not let the elusive NPK trophy slip away for a third time. Kye, Lizzy and Scott do everything in their power to derail him.

episodes.name: Biggest Street Race Ever
episodes.overview: JJ Da Boss has invited 8-street racing teams from around the country to Memphis for a chance to win $100,000. A win won't come without a fight, though, as South Carolina's small-tire racers and St. Louis high-dollar drivers are ready for war.

episodes.name: David Meet Goliath
episodes.overview: The heat is on as the South Carolina underdogs bring the fight to the St. Louis crew. It's all on display as mouthy leadership, fired-up tempers, and high pressure situations dominate a tension-filled night.

episodes.name: We Got Bad Blood
episodes.overview: The second matchup gets heated fast as Kye Kelley and his NOLA racers take on Birdman and his team from Texas. The rivals' history of bad blood comes to a head when NOLA has car trouble, and Texas refuses to play nice.

episodes.name: First-Round Knockout
episodes.overview: The war continues between Team NOLA and Texas in a matchup that comes down to who can race best under pressure. In the end, the win will ultimately go to the team who can focus on the street instead of their fists.

episodes.name: Civil War
episodes.overview: The North takes on the South in Memphis as Quinn and his family of Kentucky racers face off against Chris Rankin's ragtag team from the Northeast. Rankin's hodgepodge team hasn't raced together before but Quinn's hot head may get in the way of a win.

episodes.name: The Storm Rages On
episodes.overview: A storm is brewing as the fight between Kentucky and the Northeast continues. Rankin pushes all the buttons he can to unravel Quinn and his team, forcing JJ to intervene before the street race turns into a street brawl.

episodes.name: Spinning Ain't Winning
episodes.overview: Chucky and his infamous team from Detroit toe the line against Richard McCarver and his Mississippi racers. Chucky's ready to prove Motor City's dominance, but McCarver knows a big mouth doesn't mean you're a big deal.

episodes.name: Move Over, Motor City
episodes.overview: The final match rages on between the racers from Mississippi and the big-mouth, bigger-horsepower team from Detroit. The Motor City boys think the win is in the bag, but a surprise comeback from Richard McCarver keeps the South in the game.iered 02/11/2020

episodes.name: The Final Four
episodes.overview: Only four teams have survived to the second round of the biggest street race in history. Street-smart Chris Rankin and his Northeast crew go head-to-head against upstart Kye Kelley and his New Orleans' crew.

episodes.name: The Takedown
episodes.overview: In the second round, Chris Rankin and the Northeast face off against Kye Kelley and his New Orleans' crew. The North won't be counted out yet, but they'll need to dig deep to outrun and outgun the South.

episodes.name: Big, Bad Block
episodes.overview: The second match of round two pits Chucky and his team from Detroit against Chris Block and his South Carolina racers. Tensions have been mounting since the duo's scuffle at the last chip draw, and the $100,000 pot is fanning the flames.

episodes.name: Too Much Power
episodes.overview: The fast-paced feud between Detroit and South Carolina continues and Motor City brings more power than their cars can handle. Block's team tries to take advantage of Detroit's mistake, and the race comes down to the wire.

episodes.name: NOLA Vs. Detroit: Battle Of The Heavyweights
episodes.overview: After weeks of racing, only Detroit and NOLA remain fighting for a chance to race Memphis for $100,000. Chucky plans to keep Kye in the rearview with a new strategy to take the lead, while Kye is confident his heavy hitters can take out team Detroit.

episodes.name: NOLA Vs. Detroit: Dominate Or Go Home
episodes.overview: Teams NOLA and Detroit move into the second round of the final battle to see who will race Memphis for $100,000. Chucky Davis tries to dominate the night, while Kye Kelley makes a risky decision that could send his team home.

episodes.name: Memphis Vs. NOLA: 100 Grand Stand
episodes.overview: Memphis vs. NOLA: The final matchup is on, with $100,000 at stake. Kye Kelley's NOLA team is riding high after defeating Detroit, but JJ and the MSO won't be intimidated. Both teams are tested to their limits when they face off outside of Las Vegas.

episodes.name: Memphis Vs. NOLA: Winner Takes All
episodes.overview: Memphis vs. NOLA: When an MSO racer runs off the road, the teams barrel into Round 2 knowing any mistake can be deadly. JJ and Kye Kelley fight to get control and win $100,000 and the title of Fastest in America.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Maryland
episodes.overview: Grudge Night begins as racers prepare to do battle while learning everything they can about a new track; the 405 and Texas plan to keep their data to themselves, leaving racers without teams struggling to keep up.

episodes.name: Grudge Night New Hampshire
episodes.overview: NOLA makes moves on the 405, and Lizzy Musi joins Grudge Night for the first time; after getting rained out, Ryan and Giuseppe prepare to race in the finals.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Illinois
episodes.overview: With Team NOLA looking stronger than ever, Big Chief has a new plan for the 405 involving racers without teams; Texas brings out a big-tire car in an attempt to stay in the fight.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Idaho
episodes.overview: High altitudes wreak havoc on tunes and motors in Idaho; as NOLA surges ahead in the standings, the 405 must change their strategy to keep in the game, and solo racers bond together to form a new team.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Illinois Route 66
episodes.overview: The 405 doubles down on their strategy and outcasts come together.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Colorado
episodes.overview: The racers take on the tricky Rocky Mountain altitude in Colorado.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Ohio
episodes.overview: The 405 continues their grudge strategy and NOLA licks their wounds.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Florida
episodes.overview: The season's end is approaching and the 405 has a target on their back.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Texas
episodes.overview: The racers prepare for the final event of the season at Texas Motorplex.

episodes.name: Grudge Night Tuned Up
episodes.overview: New drivers from Cali, Detroit and more gear up to join No Prep Kings.

episodes.name: Take Back These Streets
episodes.overview: After dominating the track, the once-mighty kings of the street return to reclaim their roots. Feeling like drivers have gotten soft, Chief puts the 405 to test with the most important list shakeup ever. Chief and Murder Nova part ways.

episodes.name: A New Number One
episodes.overview: Chief, Dave, Ryan, Monza and Dominator battle for the number one spot as the list shakeup continues. Chief hopes to prove that his split with Shawn hasn't slowed him down. Ryan gets some advice from an unlikely source.

episodes.name: Turn It Up
episodes.overview: A crash causes a racer to fear that his racing days might be over.

episodes.name: Boosted to the Max
episodes.overview: A familiar face returns to the 405, bringing a new ride with big potential.

episodes.name: New King Crowned
episodes.overview: Monza challenges Ryan Martin for the number one spot on the top ten list.

episodes.name: Rise Of The Og
episodes.overview: Kamikaze returns to race against a new driver hoping to earn a spot.

episodes.name: Grinding On The Daily
episodes.overview: Farmtruck and AZN bring back an epic third annual Daily Driver contest where racers show up with everything from a golf cart to a Corvette to compete for big stacks of cash.

episodes.name: New Rules, New Road
episodes.overview: The Daily Driver field is down to 18. With a new set of rules and a new road to race on, competition gets crazy. But only one driver will take home the cash prize.

episodes.name: The Dawn of America's List
episodes.overview: OKC drivers compete in a qualifier for five spots on America's List.

episodes.name: The Cold Dark Road
episodes.overview: An OG member of the 405 pushes too far to qualify for America's List.

episodes.name: Double or Nothing
episodes.overview: The stakes ratchet up as several drivers draw back-to-back races. Daddy Dave is undefeated but Big Chief is determined to ruin his night. Dominator makes a fix on the fly while Murder Nova desperately tries to improve his record.

episodes.name: The Hard Way Back
episodes.overview: A new challenge emerges as the 405 must race back the opposite direction down the road. Drivers rise and fall as they fight for the remaining slots of America's List.

episodes.name: The Fastest in the 405
episodes.overview: The five OKC slots for America's List are almost set. Chief, Dave and Ryan have all solidified their spots. Murder Nova must conquer his toughest matchups to clinch one of the remaining spots.

episodes.name: No Weak Links
episodes.overview: Chief prepares the 405 for another America's List qualifier season.

episodes.name: Drivers on the Storm
episodes.overview: The 405 makes some of their fastest passes at Okemah ever. But when an incoming rainstorm threatens race night, the guys push their cars and each other to the limit.

episodes.name: All That Matters
episodes.overview: Murder Nova pivots his strategy after a rough start to the season. But then a member of the 405 suffers a horrific crash that makes everyone rethink their choices.

episodes.name: Salty Tunes
episodes.overview: A too-close-to-call finish sets up a major battle for the top spot.

episodes.name: By a Bumper
episodes.overview: Jeff Lutz makes his return to the streets in his GTO. But the battle for the Top 5 gets tougher than ever as racers win by the smallest margins all season.

episodes.name: Watch The Throne
episodes.overview: Ryan's quest to finish the season undefeated is put to the ultimate test when he races his three biggest competitors on the same night.

episodes.name: Unfinished Business
episodes.overview: The 405 put their camaraderie to the test with an explosive out of town race in Chicago. But it's not just the tricky Chicago crew they're worried about ... they also go head-to-head with the fastest racers from Kansas City.

episodes.name: Chase the Race
episodes.overview: The out-of-town drama escalates with fast racing, starting line disputes and fighting. And rivalries from the track are renewed on the street as the 405 faces off against heavy hitters Larry Larson and Robin Roberts.

episodes.name: Bad Blood
episodes.overview: An epic Chicago showdown comes to a first-ever dramatic daytime conclusion as the 405 attempts to prove their dominance and bitter rivals face off.

episodes.name: Last Chance
episodes.overview: It's a battle filled with upsets as the 405 spend one last night on the Chicago streets for the final rounds to determine which Top 5 will go to America's List.

18.name: Season 18
18.overview: Street Outlaws explores the world of street racing in Oklahoma City where, after throwing out the top 10 list, the 405 competes in a high-speed, high-stakes qualifier for a chance to race in America’s List.
